	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 3rd 3:29 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=28999><span id= >Domnall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>198 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here are your 5 reasons for Rangers to use a Bow.<br><br>1). Rangers Crit with the Bow. This means that you have the opportunity to crit with a weapon that has a total of 27+ damage (depending on your arrow loadout, I carry Damage 6 Steel-tipped arrows, since most of the big game I hunt is only affected with Magic weapons) and do some fairly nice ranged crits.&nbsp;&nbsp;My best is 80 so far. I have talked with other (higher level) Rangers who have done upwards of 150 or more.<br><br>2). Making the most of your Mana. If you are going to kite, you are a HECK of alot more efficient if you use arrows in addition to magic. Snare, root, bow/nuke/bow/nuke etc till root breaks, root and resnare, bow/nuke/bow/nuke etc...  You don't even have to nuke if you want to conserve your mana even further, just root and snare. Not to mention that your bow does more average damage than your nuke does till you pick up Careless Lightning at level 39.<br><br>3). Casting Damage vs Arrow Damage. As I explained in the last paragraph, your arrows will average better damage than your nukes until you get to 39. However, you will ALWAYS be able to do more total damage with arrows than you will casting, as you can carry more arrows than you will have mana to cast nukes with. Think I am Crazy?  I have a Tailored Quiver with 6 slots. 20 arrows per slot. Another 20 in my ammo slot. With an average of 15 points per arrow (that is what I average, BTW, including crits and misses) and 140 arrows, vs about 70 points (probably less, I was figuring less resists from doing only blues) and 900 mana (about 13 casts, more or less, not figuring for fizzles).<br><br>4). Pulling.  If you are running low on mana, which way is better to pull with?  Shoot it with an arrow and stay clear of it, or running up to it and hitting on it with a melee weapon so it has the chance to start hitting you (and possibly stunning you so it can hit you some more)? Heck, why even run low on mana by pulling with spells in the first place? If you snare while it is a ways out, you run the risk of it running into it's friends while coming after you on a slow jog. He tells a friend or two and suddenly what started as an easy pull turns into a nightmare. Save your mana.<br><br>5). A way to still deal out some damage if you have to back out cause you are hurt. If you can successfully pull back from a melee engagement because you are hurting (not a fun thing, but sometimes necessary), then allow the tank to reaqquire the top hate spot and start shooting at it from a distance. It is slow enough that you usually won't get the agro off the main tank again, and if you do the tank has enough time to reagro the critter again.<br><br>As for Earthcaller and Ebon Razor.  YEAH RIGHT! Earthcaller is NO DROP and cannot be multi quested because almost all of the items involved in the quest are turned in ONE AT A TIME, and some pieces are dependent on success by the character on killing a VERY high level NPC/MoB on another Plane, which you can't even do until 46 minimum.<br><a href="http://www.questing-ranger.com/quests/epic_quest.html" target=_new>http://www.questing-ranger.com/quests/epic_quest.html</a><br>Ebon Razor is not usable by a Ranger. PERIOD. <br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics11/ebonrazor.JPG" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics11/ebonrazor.JPG</a><br>RANGERS CANNOT BE AGNOSTIC! YOU CAN ONLY CHOOSE TUNARE OR KARANA!<br><br>Please, at least research your items and class before you claim to use them or be one. At least then you won't make yourself look so bad. But then again, that is why you posted as Anonymous. Get a life and get out of the boards if you are gonna post this kind of nonsense. If you play the game like you post, I hope you are on a PvP server so you get your butt owned daily by a player who knows what they are doing.<br><br>For those that see this and wonder about the level of my response, change your forum Preferences-Filter from "Default Filter" to "Never Filter" and you will see the original poster's comment that started this reply series.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
